Posts.Content: Mar 14, 2012 12:49PM Blahblahblah326 wrote: Chiming in here a little late, but my stereotactic biopsy was easy peasy. I felt nothing, but a slight pinch. I was more annoyed by the numb and heavy feeling I had in my left breast. I went about my business that day. I iced it on and off for an hour or so and I was good to go. I was terrorfied from reading on line. I was actually crying from anxiety and by the time the procedure was over I felt like a fool... Hang in there!
